公司的主导地位。她的报告批评美国反垄断法过于关注消费者价格，而忽视了公司可以通过其他方式违法以获得竞争优势。 “作为消费者、用户，我们热爱这些科技公司，”她在 2018 年<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2018/09/07/technology/monopoly-antitrust-lina-khan-amazon.html">告诉</a><em>《纽约时报》。</em> “但作为公民、工人和企业家，我们认识到他们的力量令人不安。我们需要一个新的框架、一个新的词汇来评估和解决他们的主导地位。”亚马逊根据汗的学术工作和之前的陈述， <a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.washingtonpost.com/technology/2021/06/30/amazon-khan-ftc-recusal/">主张</a>汗回避此案。</p><p>据报道，拜登政府“越来越担心” <a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/hitting-the-books-access-rules-mayer-schonberger-ramge-uc-press-140054547.html">大型科技公司的影响力</a>。<em>彭博社</em>将行政部门<a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2023-08-07/amazon-to-meet-with-ftc-next-week-in-final-push-to-avoid-suit">描述</a>为“寻求扭转数十年来对企业整合和市场力量监管松懈的局面”。美国司法部已多次<a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/ftc-reportedly-loses-court-order-to-block-metas-acquisition-of-vr-developer-within-172220645.html">起诉 Meta</a>和<a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/justice-department-sues-google-to-break-up-the-companys-digital-ad-business-190131636.html">谷歌</a>（尽管联邦法官最近<a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/federal-judge-narrows-scope-of-antitrust-case-against-google-ahead-of-trial-202837725.html">缩小了其中一个案件的范围</a>）。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/amazon-will-reportedly-meet-with-the-ftc-ahead-of-pottial-antitrust-lawsuit-190316632.html?src=rss]] >; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/amazon-will-reportedly-meet-with-the-ftc-ahead-of-potential-antitrust-lawsuit-190316632.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 63729573-ec0f-41d1-a3c1-1c1154492f27</guid><dc:creator>威尔·尚克林</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Mon, 07 Aug 2023 19:03:16 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1691434998</ingested><modified> 2023-08-07T19:03:33+00:00 </